<%= button_to 'Undo', '/waves/undolist', :method => "get" %>
<%= button_to 'Update Numbers', '/waves/update_nums', :method => "get", remote: true %> 
<p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>
<br>


<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Wave number</th>
      <th>Start time</th>
      <th colspan="3"></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>

  <tbody>
    <% @waves.sort_by { |x| [x.wave_number] }.reverse.each do |wave| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= wave.wave_number %></td>
        <% Time.zone = "Singapore" %>
        <td><%= wave.start_time %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Show', wave %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_wave_path(wave) %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', wave, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' } %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>

<br>

<br>
<h2 class = "fronttitle">Instructions</h2>
<p class="instructions">FOR START TIMER</p>
<p class="instructions">1) Work with the TAGGERS to release each wave smoothly. Only release a wave when you know the TAGGERS have completed tagging that wave.</p>
<p class="instructions">To prevent an abrupt start to the race, make use of the timer which will be shown to the runners and release the wave when the timer hits 0.</p>
<p class="instructions">2) Tap "=" when you release the wave to record the timing for the Wave.</p>

<h2 class = "fronttitle">Problems</h2>
<p class="instructions">1) IN CASE YOU TAPPED "=" TWICE: Delete the wrong wave by clicking "Destroy"</p>
<p class="instructions">2) IN CASE YOU DELETED A WRONG WAVE: Click "Undo" and restore the wave you deleted</p>
